item.title: Apparmor="DENIED" operation="file_mmap" parent=15709 profile="/home/*/tor-browse
item.dc:creator: TNT_BOM_BOM
item.description:
Unrelated to AppArmor. These are developer level information. Not very helpful to users. Naturally, if you watch closely, you see things. These information can be useful for debugging if you had issues with a Tor connection. As long as everything is working, these messages are not worth being reported. Don't take arm too serious. On the other hand, if many users had connection troubles, and many users would report these messages, then it would give the Tor developers a clue what is going on.

thought every message which is inside the apparmor then its related to it.

AppArmor denied messages: How to reproduce? Which website did you visit? Installed any additional plugin? Visited some plugin testing website?

how to reproduce? => dont know , but i will try on a different workstation

which website did you visit? => non in specific , just being here or the image uploading website…

installed any additional plugin? => nope

Visited some plugin testing website?=> nope
